   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>In the Old Testament: The divine economy concerning the tabernacle, the offerings, and the priests: God charged the people of Israel to build the tabernacle typifying Christ for His dwelling and to serve Him by the priests through the offerings both typifying Christ Exo 25 Lev 27.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>Israel entered into the good land Josh 3 4.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>Israel set up the tabernacle of the ark in Shiloh Josh 18:1.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>The satanic chaos with the priests: The priests among Israel became degraded 1 Sam 2:12-17, 22-34.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>The ark was captured by Israel's enemy 1 Sam 4:1 5:2.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>The divine economy with David, Solomon, and the positive prophets: God raised up David as a man after His own heart to do His will 1 Sam 13:14.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>David brought back the ark of God 2 Sam 6:1-19.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>David desired to build the temple for God and prepared the material and the site for the building of God's temple 2 Sam 7:2; 1 Chron 22:1-19; 29:1-19; 2 Chron 3:1.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>Solomon built the temple for God and brought the ark into the temple 1 Kings 5:4-5; 6:2; 7:51 8:11.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>The positive prophets ministered faithfully, especially concerning Christ in the divine economy.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>The satanic chaos with the kings, the priests, the prophets, and the people: David fell into sin, and his family became a mess 2 Sam 11 18.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>Solomon fell into sin, and his kingdom was divided into two 1 Kings 11:1-40.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>The decline of the kings, the corruption of the priests, the falsehood of the prophets, and the evils of the people of Israel were intolerable, as recorded in 1 and 2 Kings and the books of the prophets.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>Jerusalem was destroyed, the temple was burned, and the people of Israel were captured by the Babylonians 2 Chron 36:17-20.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>The divine economy with the returned captives: The captives returned to their fathers' land Ezra 1.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>The temple of God with the altar for the offerings typifying Christ was rebuilt Ezra 3.</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>The returned remnant of David brought forth Christ as their Messiah in His first coming Matt 1:1, 6b-16; Luke 3:22-31.</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>The satanic chaos with the returned captives: The returned captives were idle in building the temple of God Hag 1.</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>The returned captives were in a messy situation, as dealt with in the books of Nehemiah, Haggai, and Malachi.</S>
   </TEXT>
